# Implementation Plan - Hybrid Hermes-4.3-36B Integration

The goal is to integrate the `Hermes-4.3-36B` model as a primary components within the Cosmos CNS using a **Hybrid Cascade** approach. Since the local PC has 16GB RAM and limited VRAM, we will use a small local model for speed and offload heavy reasoning to a cloud-hosted Hermes-36B.

## Proposed Changes

### [Cosmos Core]

#### [MODIFY] [model_manager.py](file:///d:/Cosmos/Cosmos/core/model_manager.py)
- Define a `hermes-36b-cloud` model profile.
- Configure it to use `BackendType.OPENAI_COMPATIBLE` or `BackendType.GEMINI` (pointing to a Hermes-compatible endpoint like OpenRouter).
- Ensure a local "companion" model (e.g., `qwen2.5-1.5b` or `phi-3.5-mini`) is defined for the cascade base.

#### [MODIFY] [llm_backend.py](file:///d:/Cosmos/Cosmos/core/llm_backend.py)
- Update [CascadeBackend](file:///d:/Cosmos/Cosmos/core/llm_backend.py#1227-1353) to support a local-to-cloud transition.
- Implement specialized "Complexity Estimation" for Hermes-specific tasks (RL feedback, skill synthesis).

### [Cosmos Integration]

#### [MODIFY] [hermes_bridge.py](file:///d:/Cosmos/Cosmos/integration/hermes_bridge.py)
- Configure the [HermesRuntime](file:///d:/Cosmos/Cosmos/integration/hermes_bridge.py#505-639) to use the [CascadeBackend](file:///d:/Cosmos/Cosmos/core/llm_backend.py#1227-1353).
- This allows the Hermes AIAgent to start fast on local hardware but escalate to the full 36B model for complex plans/coding.

